<br>
However, I do not care how many of the enemies civilians die, as long as it gives our forces a strategic or tactical advantage.  If it saves one life on our side, then in my eyes it is worth it.<br>
<br>
I wish, as do all my friends who are preparing to go into harms way, that this was not a need.  None of us want to see friends go into battle, then possibly not return.  We do not want to see our families, friends, or neighboors die.  This is not something we the US chose, it was not a decision that we made.   We have tried to be kind to every country and every faction in the world that we could.  The result is we are despised through out much of the world that we send money, food, medicines etc too every year.  <br>
<br>
So do I wish to see civilians die?  That answer is a huge no.  Do I accept the fact that it will happen?  That answer is yes.<br>
